e stars belonging to this\nnew branch are supported against collapse by the nonlocal effects of the bulk\non the brane. We also show that these stars are always stable under small\nradial perturbations. These results support the idea that traces of\nextra-dimensions might be found in astrophysics, specifically through the\nanalysis of masses and radii of compact objects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 25 Feb 2017 03:05:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-01"}
